Service File:

In order to automatically run a python script when booted, a 'service' file is needed.

To enable or disable a service script, use the command:

sudo systemctl enable waypoint_janus.service


To create one, do:
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/waypoint_janus.service

And in it, paste a script like:

[Unit]
Description=Waypoint Janus Control Service
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=arratialab
WorkingDirectory=/home/arratialab/Documents/DroneScripts
ExecStart=/home/arratialab/droneenv/bin/python /home/arratialab/Documents/DroneScripts/waypoint_janus_control.py
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=5

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

Reload systemd daemon to recognize the new service:

sudo systemctl daemon-reload

Enable the service to start on boot:

sudo systemctl enable waypoint_janus.service

Start the service now (or reboot to test auto-start):

sudo systemctl start waypoint_janus.service

Check the status or logs for troubleshooting:

sudo systemctl status waypoint_janus.service
sudo journalctl -u waypoint_janus.service -f

